  "text": "Envoy's certificate validation code is located in two primary locations: source/common/tls/ and source/extensions/transport_sockets/tls/. The default validator in source/common/tls/cert_validator/default_validator.cc handles both server and client certificate validation through the DefaultCertValidator class.\n\nSERVER CERTIFICATE VALIDATION (Client-side):\nWhen Envoy acts as a client connecting to upstream servers, certificate validation is performed through a custom verification callback chain:\n1. source/common/tls/context_impl.cc defines customVerifyCallback (line 474) which is set via SSL_CTX_set_custom_verify (line 181)\n2. This callback delegates to customVerifyCertChain which invokes cert_validator_->doVerifyCertChain\n3. source/common/tls/cert_validator/default_validator.cc implements doVerifyCertChain (line 280) which:\n   - Creates an X509_STORE_CTX for the certificate chain\n   - Calls X509_verify_cert (line 315) to validate the chain against trusted CAs\n   - Performs Subject Alternative Name (SAN) matching\n   - Validates certificate hashes and SPKI if configured\n   - Returns ValidationResults with detailed status\n4. source/common/tls/utility.cc provides getX509VerificationErrorInfo (line 457) to extract error details from X509_verify_cert failures\n\nCLIENT CERTIFICATE VALIDATION (Server-side):\nWhen Envoy acts as a server, client certificate validation is configured through:\n1. source/common/tls/server_context_impl.cc (line 147-149) calls cert_validator_->addClientValidationContext when not using a custom handshaker\n2. source/common/tls/cert_validator/default_validator.cc implements addClientValidationContext (line 481) which:\n   - Loads trusted client CA certificates into the SSL_CTX\n   - Calls SSL_CTX_set_client_CA_list to set the list of CAs\n   - Optionally calls SSL_CTX_set_verify (line 528) with SSL_VERIFY_PEER | SSL_VERIFY_FAIL_IF_NO_PEER_CERT when requireClientCertificate is true\n   - Sets SSL_CTX_set_verify_depth for maximum chain depth validation\n3. source/common/tls/context_impl.cc initializes verification mode via initializeSslContexts (line 164-167) which sets verify_mode flags used by SSL_CTX_set_custom_verify\n\nVERIFICATION MODE FLAGS:\nThe verify_mode variable (controlled in source/common/tls/cert_validator/default_validator.cc lines 59-112) determines verification behavior:\n- SSL_VERIFY_NONE: No peer verification\n- SSL_VERIFY_PEER: Verify peer certificate if provided\n- SSL_VERIFY_FAIL_IF_NO_PEER_CERT: Require peer certificate\nThese are set in SSL_CTX_set_custom_verify (line 181 in context_impl.cc) for custom verification or SSL_CTX_set_verify (line 528 in default_validator.cc) for client validation.\n\nSPIFFE VALIDATOR EXTENSION:\nsource/extensions/transport_sockets/tls/cert_validator/spiffe/spiffe_validator.cc extends default validation for SPIFFE (Secure Production Identity Framework For Everyone) with trust domain-based validation. It also uses X509_verify_cert (line 177) against domain-specific trust bundles.\n\nKEY FILES HANDLING VALIDATION LOGIC:\n- source/common/tls/cert_validator/default_validator.{cc,h}: Core validation logic\n- source/common/tls/context_impl.{cc,h}: Context initialization and custom verify callback\n- source/common/tls/server_context_impl.cc: Server-side client certificate setup\n- source/common/tls/utility.cc: Error handling and certificate utilities\n- source/extensions/transport_sockets/tls/cert_validator/spiffe/spiffe_validator.cc: SPIFFE-specific validation"
